docs.abstract: Chasing a “moment,” the show at the Super Bowl in 1995 is remembered as peak circus act. And it scared the “bejeebers” out of Patti LaBelle.
docs.snippet: Chasing a “moment,” the show at the Super Bowl in 1995 is remembered as peak circus act. And it scared the “bejeebers” out of Patti LaBelle.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Dale Girard was wearing long underwear covered in what he said looked like “ectoplasmic slime from ‘Ghostbusters’” but was actually freezing cold fire gel. Costumed as “The Executioner,” he was in a holding area underneath a massive metal stage as it was being rolled onto the field at what was then known as Joe Robbie Stadium.

headline.main: Shakira? J. Lo? This Halftime Show Had Snakes and Indiana Jones
headline.print_headline: What Do Indiana Jones, Patti LaBelle and ‘The Lion King’ Have in Common?

docs.abstract: When countries clash, here’s what happens to those of us caught in the middle.
docs.snippet: When countries clash, here’s what happens to those of us caught in the middle.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Soon after I was informed in mid-March that my journalist visa for China had been canceled, I faced a dilemma: what to do with my collection of wooden staffs used in a style of Chinese martial arts that I had been practicing for nearly 10 years.

headline.main: Kicked Out of China, and Other Real-Life Costs of a Geopolitical Meltdown
headline.print_headline: Real-Life Costs of a Geopolitical Meltdown

docs.abstract: Edward Markey, 74, entered Congress before Joseph Kennedy III was born. But in their Senate race he has harnessed the energy of Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and the ascendant left, much to Mr. Kennedy’s frustration.

docs.lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Stepping out of the rain on a dreary Saturday morning, Representative Joseph P. Kennedy III made no attempt to hide his frustration as he raced from neighborhood to neighborhood in a city as synonymous with his family as it is with the Green Monster.

headline.main: In Massachusetts, Markey Outflanks Kennedy by Running as Bold Insurgent

docs.abstract: In 1918, Ulrich Bonnell Phillips published “American Negro Slavery,” which framed slavery as a labor agreement between masters and happy slaves — facile thinking that persists today.
docs.snippet: In 1918, Ulrich Bonnell Phillips published “American Negro Slavery,” which framed slavery as a labor agreement between masters and happy slaves — facile thinking that persists today.
docs.lead_paragraph: A video of the rapper Kanye West discussing slavery is a sad reminder of America’s historical amnesia about the brutal realities of that institution. “When you hear about slavery for 400 years,” he said in the clip, which was widely circulated on Twitter, “that sounds like a choice.”

headline.main: The Historian Behind Slavery Apologists Like Kanye West
